President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. The nominees include Dr. Steven E. Koonin for Under Secretary for Science at the Department of Energy, David Sandalow for Assistant Secretary for Policy and International Affairs at the Department of Energy, Ambassador Johnnie Carson for Assistant Secretary for African Affairs at the State Department, Kathy Martinez for Assistant Secretary for Disability Employment Policy at the Department of Labor, Jonathan S. Adelstein for Administrator for the Rural Utilities Service at the Department of Agriculture, Timothy W. Manning for Deputy Administrator for National Preparedness at FEMA, and Priscilla E. Guthrie for Chief Information Officer at the Office of Director of National Intelligence. President Obama also announced that Steve Isakowitz will continue serving as the Chief Financial Officer at the Department of Energy.